# Command gitme

## What does this command do:

Easily find local Git repos

## Installed from

For Fedora install using: `git clone https://github.com/davorg/gitme > ~/bin/gitme`
For Raspberry Pi install using: `git clone https://github.com/davorg/gitme > ~/bin/gitme`
For Mac install using: `git clone https://github.com/davorg/gitme > ~/bin/gitme`

## Command path

For Fedora run: `source $HOME/bin/gitme/gitme`
For Raspberry Pi run: `source $HOME/bin/gitme/gitme`
For Mac run: `source $HOME/bin/gitme/gitme`

## Command documentation

Docs can be found at https://github.com/davorg/gitme

## Command options

# Jump to a repo by name or partial name
gitme <search-term>

# Jump to a repo matching a remote URL or fragment
gitme github.com/davorg

# Rebuild the repository cache (faster searching)
gitme --rebuild-cache

# Show help
gitme --help

# Show version
gitme --version
